{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":810,"text":"I'd like to tell you a story\nabout death and architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4841,"text":"A hundred years ago, we tended to die\nof infectious diseases like pneumonia,"},{"time":9471,"text":"that, if they took hold,\nwould take us away quite quickly."},{"time":12768,"text":"We tended to die at home,\nin our own beds, looked after by family,"},{"time":16502,"text":"although that was the default option"},{"time":18294,"text":"because a lot of people\nlacked access to medical care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21614,"text":"And then in the 20th century\na lot of things changed."},{"time":24393,"text":"We developed new medicines like penicillin"},{"time":26490,"text":"so we could treat\nthose infectious diseases."},{"time":28975,"text":"New medical technologies\nlike x-ray machines were invented."},{"time":32249,"text":"And because they were\nso big and expensive,"},{"time":34501,"text":"we needed large, centralized\nbuildings to keep them in,"},{"time":37519,"text":"and they became our modern hospitals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39818,"text":"After the Second World War,"},{"time":41241,"text":"a lot of countries set up \nuniversal healthcare systems"},{"time":43881,"text":"so that everyone who needed\ntreatment could get it."},{"time":46528,"text":"The result was that lifespans extended\nfrom about 45 at the start of the century"},{"time":50777,"text":"to almost double that today."},{"time":52960,"text":"The 20th century was this time of huge \noptimism about what science could offer,"},{"time":57058,"text":"but with all of the focus on life,\ndeath was forgotten,"},{"time":60785,"text":"even as our approach to death\nchanged dramatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63580,"text":"Now, I'm an architect,"},{"time":64783,"text":"and for the past year and a half\nI've been looking at these changes"},{"time":68025,"text":"and at what they mean for architecture\nrelated to death and dying."},{"time":71179,"text":"We now tend to die\nof cancer and heart disease,"},{"time":74412,"text":"and what that means is that many of us\nwill have a long period of chronic illness"},{"time":78408,"text":"at the end of our lives."},{"time":80382,"text":"During that period,"},{"time":81495,"text":"we'll likely spend a lot of time \nin hospitals and hospices and care homes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86558,"text":"Now, we've all been in a modern hospital."},{"time":88764,"text":"You know those fluorescent lights\nand the endless corridors"},{"time":92154,"text":"and those rows of uncomfortable chairs."},{"time":95172,"text":"Hospital architecture\nhas earned its bad reputation."},{"time":98934,"text":"But the surprising thing is,\nit wasn't always like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102091,"text":"This is L'Ospedale degli Innocenti,\nbuilt in 1419 by Brunelleschi,"},{"time":106425,"text":"who was one of the most famous\nand influential architects of his time."},{"time":110172,"text":"And when I look at this building\nand then think about hospitals today,"},{"time":113515,"text":"what amazes me is\nthis building's ambition."},{"time":116603,"text":"It's just a really great building."},{"time":118252,"text":"It has these courtyards in the middle"},{"time":120086,"text":"so that all of the rooms\nhave daylight and fresh air,"},{"time":122619,"text":"and the rooms are big\nand they have high ceilings,"},{"time":125032,"text":"so they just feel\nmore comfortable to be in."},{"time":127516,"text":"And it's also beautiful."},{"time":129281,"text":"Somehow, we've forgotten\nthat that's even possible for a hospital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133112,"text":"Now, if we want better buildings\nfor dying, then we have to talk about it,"},{"time":137135,"text":"but because we find the subject\nof death uncomfortable,"},{"time":139706,"text":"we don't talk about it,"},{"time":141146,"text":"and we don't question how we\nas a society approach death."},{"time":144458,"text":"One of the things that surprised me\nmost in my research, though,"},{"time":147632,"text":"is how changeable attitudes actually are."},{"time":150317,"text":"This is the first crematorium in the U.K.,"},{"time":152709,"text":"which was built in Woking in the 1870s."},{"time":155518,"text":"And when this was first built,\nthere were protests in the local village."},{"time":158925,"text":"Cremation wasn't socially acceptable,\nand 99.8 percent of people got buried."},{"time":163808,"text":"And yet, only a hundred years later,\nthree quarters of us get cremated."},{"time":167584,"text":"People are actually really open\nto changing things"},{"time":170111,"text":"if they're given the chance\nto talk about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172512,"text":"So this conversation\nabout death and architecture"},{"time":175835,"text":"was what I wanted to start\nwhen I did my first exhibition on it"},{"time":178994,"text":"in Venice in June,\nwhich was called \"Death in Venice.\""},{"time":182220,"text":"It was designed to be quite playful"},{"time":185494,"text":"so that people would\nliterally engage with it."},{"time":187692,"text":"This is one of our exhibits,\nwhich is an interactive map of London"},{"time":190947,"text":"that shows just how much\nof the real estate in the city"},{"time":193622,"text":"is given over to death and dying,"},{"time":195501,"text":"and as you wave your hand across the map,"},{"time":197870,"text":"the name of that piece of real estate,\nthe building or cemetery, is revealed."},{"time":202699,"text":"Another of our exhibits\nwas a series of postcards"},{"time":205207,"text":"that people could take away with them."},{"time":207204,"text":"And they showed people's homes\nand hospitals"},{"time":209665,"text":"and cemeteries and mortuaries,"},{"time":212080,"text":"and they tell the story\nof the different spaces"},{"time":214541,"text":"that we pass through\non either side of death."},{"time":217374,"text":"We wanted to show\nthat where we die"},{"time":219719,"text":"is a key part of how we die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222970,"text":"Now, the strangest thing was the way\nthat visitors reacted to the exhibition,"},{"time":227753,"text":"especially the audio-visual works."},{"time":230121,"text":"We had people dancing\nand running and jumping"},{"time":233813,"text":"as they tried to activate\nthe exhibits in different ways,"},{"time":236808,"text":"and at a certain point\nthey would kind of stop"},{"time":239252,"text":"and remember that they were in\nan exhibition about death,"},{"time":241986,"text":"and that maybe that's not\nhow you're supposed to act."},{"time":244610,"text":"But actually, I would question\nwhether there is one way"},{"time":247257,"text":"that you're supposed to act around death,"},{"time":249532,"text":"and if there's not, I'd ask you to think\nabout what you think a good death is,"},{"time":254083,"text":"and what you think that architecture\nthat supports a good death might be like,"},{"time":257752,"text":"and mightn't it be a little less like this\nand a little more like this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262480,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264694,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}